<div tiddler="StoryColumn" modifier="JeremyRuston" modified="200511221924" created="200511221924" tags="overview">The StoryColumn is the main reading area of TiddlyWiki; the place where new tiddlers are opened. It is rendered as:\n{{{\n&lt;div id='tiddlerDisplay'&gt;\n&lt;!-- contains multiple tiddlers, each looking like this: --&gt;\n&lt;div id='tiddler&lt;title&gt;' class='tiddler selected shadow missing'\n    tiddler='&lt;title&gt;' tags='&lt;tags&gt;'&gt;\n   &lt;!-- rendered tiddler content goes here --&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n}}}\n\nSome of the classes are context sensitive:\n* ''selected'' is set for the tiddler under the mouse\n* ''shadow'' is set for tiddlers that are missing but have a shadow value\n* ''missing'' is set for tiddlers that are missing, and don't have a shadow value\n\nThe {{{tags}}} attribute is there so you can write CSS rules that target specific tiddlers by tag:\n{{{\ndiv[tags~=&quot;welcome&quot;].viewer {\nbackground-color: #ffccaa;\n}\n\ndiv[tags~=&quot;features&quot;].viewer {\nbackground-color: #88aaff;\n}\n}}}\n\nThe individual tiddlers are rendered by the TiddlerTemplateMechanism.\n</div>